{"word":"τμήγω","slug":"τμήγω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>τμήγω</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b>epic form of <el>τέμνω</el>\n<p/><div class='li750'><b>1. </b><i>to cut, cleave</i>: <a href='S:Medium, Middle'>Mid.</a>, <el>ὁδὸν ἐτμήξαντο</el> <i>cut their</i> way, <b><a href='S:Anthology'>Anth.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><a href='S:metaphorically'>metaph.</a> in aor2 <a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>pass.</a></a> <i>to be divided</i> or <i>dispersed, to part</i>, <b><a href='S:Iliad'>Il.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}